abstract: LONDON, June 2 -- In the debate to-day on an amendment offered by Mr. E.W. abstract: The wave of excitement which swept over the City of Chicago during the last four days, and which caused a general and rather heavy run on the savings banks of that city, has apparently subsided. abstract: For some weeks pedestrians in Lorimer Street, Brooklyn, during the early morning hours have been accosted by rough characters that asked for from 10 cents to $1. About 1 o'clock yesterday morning George Smith, twenty-three years old, of 111 Withers Street, Williamsburg, was held up by two footpads and, upon refusing to give them a dollar, was shot through the left side, just below the heart.

abstract: JERSEY CITY, N.J., June 24 -- The City Hall Commissioners had an exciting meeting to-day, in which Contractor Patrick J. Condon took an active part. abstract: There was a good holiday crowd at the Sheepshead Bay races yesterday, but the sport was of a very commonplace sort for this track. abstract: CHICAGO, June 27 -- The people sold wheat to-day who bought it yesterday. Timely rains where needed for Spring wheat unsettled the bull sentiment. abstract: New-York. -- Annie Sheehan was acquitted yesterday of the charge or manslaughter in the Court of General Sessions.
